 and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 4<b>. Place simmering basket instead of measuring cup on mixing bowl lid and sauté <strong>30 min\/250°F\/\/speed <\/strong>."},{"content":"Add bourbon, scrape bottom of mixing bowl with spatula and sauté a further <strong>15 min\/250°F\/\/speed <\/strong>. Transfer to a bowl and keep warm."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Cooking Burgers and Assembly"},{"content":"Season patties with salt and cook over medium high heat on a grill or stovetop to taste (see Tip)."},{"content":"Spread ketchup on bottom bun, add patty and top with cheese, Bourbon Glazed Onions, tomatoes, butter lettuce and top bun. Serve immediately."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Buffalo meat has very little fat and is best cooked rare. Buffalo rare is approximately 135°F, medium is approximately 140°F, and well done is approximately160°F.","Ground buffalo meat can be replaced with buffalo meat. To grind buffalo meat: place a zip lock bag onto mixing bowl lid and weigh in 8 oz buffalo meat that has been cut into1 inch pieces. Repeat this step with another zip lock bag with remaining 8 oz buffalo meat and place both bags in freezer until partially frozen (approx.1 hour). Place one 8 oz bag of frozen buffalo meat into mixing bowl after chopping shallots and grind <strong>5 sec\/speed 6<\/strong>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside. Place remaining 8 oz bag of frozen buffalo meat into mixing bowl and grind <strong><b>5 sec\/speed 6<b><\/strong>. Add reserved ground buffalo and shallots and mix together <strong>5 sec\/\/speed 4<\/strong>. Use spatula to evenly combine before proceeding with recipe."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","1h 10m","4 portions"]}